 P(Y_n = np) = {n \choose np} p^{np} (1-p)^{n-np}. 
 P(Y_n = np) = {n! \over (np)! (nq)!} (p^p q^q)^n. 
n! \sim \sqrt{2\pi n} \left( {n \over e} \right)^n. 
 P(Y_n = np) \sim {\sqrt{2\pi n} (n/e)^n \over \sqrt{2\pi pn} (pn/e)^{pn} \sqrt{2\pi qn} (qn/e)^{qn}} (p^p q^q)^n 
 P(Y_n = np) \sim {1 \over \sqrt{2\pi npq}}. 
 P(Y_n = n/2) \sim {1 \over \sqrt{n \pi/2}} \approx {0.8 \over \sqrt{n}}. 
